<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<beans xmlns="http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans"
       xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
       xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans
        http://www.springframework.org/schema/beans/spring-beans.xsd">

    <bean id="xmlEmployee" class="com.spring.ioc.SpringIoc.xmlconfig.beans.XmlEmployee"/>
    <bean id="xmlOrganisation" class="com.spring.ioc.SpringIoc.xmlconfig.beans.XmlOrganisation"/>
    <bean id="xmlAddress" class="com.spring.ioc.SpringIoc.xmlconfig.beans.XmlAddress"/>

</beans>

<!--
id attribute of bean element is used to register a bean in Spring Ioc. We can retrieve a bean
by using its id or its Class name from the Spring Ioc.

Default Scope for bean element is singleton.

<bean> element is converted into BeanDefinition object and is maintained by Spring
Ioc(ApplicationContext).

Refer : BasicBeanDefinition.Java
-->